            <li><strong>Expert Repair:</strong> We carry common parts on our trucks for faster repairs</li>
            <li><strong>Cooling Restored:</strong> Most emergency repairs are completed the same visit</li>
          </ol>

          <h2>While You Wait for Emergency Service</h2>
          <p>If your AC has failed and you're waiting for our technician, here are some tips to stay safe and cool:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Check your thermostat:</strong> Make sure it's set to "cool" and the temperature is set below current room temperature</li>
            <li><strong>Check your breaker:</strong> Try resetting the AC breaker if it's tripped</li>
            <li><strong>Check your filter:</strong> A severely clogged filter can cause system shutdown</li>
            <li><strong>Close blinds and curtains:</strong> Block out sunlight to reduce heat gain</li>
            <li><strong>Use fans:</strong> Ceiling and portable fans help circulate air</li>
            <li><strong>Stay hydrated:</strong> Drink plenty of water, especially if you're elderly or have health conditions</li>
            <li><strong>Relocate if necessary:</strong> If temperatures become dangerous, move to a cooler location</li>
          </ul>

